CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 2, 1959, pg. 12, reads: "Love's Labor's Lost...Sometimes Home is Where the Heart Remains - Built by Jennie Proctor - Another pioneer home builder was Mrs. Jennie Proctor who built the above apartment building for her people at 2850 Webster Ave. It is now owned by whites but still occupied by Negroes.  Mrs. Proctor was a highly respected businesswoman and would have wished that her own people retain this property as evidence of their interest in preserving it for themselves."
TitMainTitle: Three story brick apartment building at 2850 Webster Avenue, with Pittsburgh Fire Department Engine House No. 26 on left, Hill District
